reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great coffee table with slight difficulty assembling
reviews.reviewText: This coffee table fits well in our smallish living room. The wood veneer is a very nice color and looks like it will be pretty scratch resistant. The metal legs are well made with clean welds, and the table is sturdy once assembled. The corners are fairly sharp, so use some cation if you have little kids.The table was fairly easy to assemble, with a couple of things that might cause trouble for someone who hasn’t assembled many of these before. The first thing I found was a couple of the threads for the fixed nuts in the legs still had some metal that wasn’t cleared. The screws would not go in at all, so I had to get my tap set and clean them out. You may be able to clean them with a heavy metal brush. The second issue was a little more minor, but the legs didn’t quite line up well when being assembled, so make sure to very loosely put the screws in until everyone is in and they are lined up, once you do that they can be tightened and will be straight when it’s all together.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This thing is solid. I originally had it as my coffee table and loved it, but got one with a lift-up top, so this became the TV stand. It holds my 65" TV perfectly and is very sturdy. I would not put the tv on this table if I didn't completely trust it, and it's done me well so far! Good looking piece and absolutely solid. Pretty easy to put together too!
